name: Reuters
text:
Today marks one month since George Floyd, a 46-year-old Black man, died after a white police officer knelt on his neck for 8 minutes and 46 seconds. 

One month ago, a video shows him saying ‘I can’t breathe’ https://t.co/9Cr35e3qSd 1/17 https://t.co/ACZ9S9KpGp

name: Reuters
text: May 26: Protests begin in Minneapolis and the four officers present at Floyd's detention are fired https://t.co/FfERoStDYG 2/17 https://t.co/AGadW3AF8T

name: Reuters
text:
May 27: Protesters gather around Minneapolis's Third Precinct police station chanting ‘No justice, no peace’ and ‘I can't breathe.’ 

Police use tear gas, plastic bullets and concussion grenades to keep the crowds at bay. 

A nearby Target is looted https://t.co/2vPM4Ih79J 3/17 https://t.co/jzLiWxDMob

name: Reuters
text:
May 28, 29: Minnesota activates the National Guard. Derek Chauvin, the officer who held Floyd down, is charged with third-degree murder. 

Trump holds a news conference, but doesn’t answer questions on Floyd https://t.co/kXlSJ4IWYJ 4/17 https://t.co/iacbNPaYXl

name: Reuters
text:
May 30, 31: Multiple cities impose curfews. 

Tens of thousands of Americans protest across the country. 

A truck drives into protesters in Minneapolis. 

National Guard troops are called into over a dozen states. https://t.co/fJkTC1nxmq 5/17 https://t.co/FytqeqBJQy

name: Reuters
text:
June 1: Protests spread overseas https://t.co/IQ03EuID2W 

U.S. Park Police deploy tear gas and pepper balls to disperse peaceful protesters outside the White House 6/17 https://t.co/U8pIjgenLA

name: Reuters
text: June 3: Three former Minneapolis police officers implicated in Floyd’s death are charged with aiding and abetting second-degree murder and manslaughter https://t.co/If9ultNmkL 7/17 https://t.co/LnQyYetmXK

name: Reuters
text:
June 4: Police in Buffalo, New York, are suspended after video shows them shoving a 75-year-old man to the ground, with his head bleeding https://t.co/OgE1FBEvTY 

Virginia governor orders the removal of a statue of Confederate General Robert E. Lee https://t.co/BSL456PYCo 8/17 https://t.co/GikIlXprbY

name: Reuters
text:
June 5-7: NFL commissioner says the league was wrong not to listen to player protests https://t.co/XJWnMqTcN2 

A statue of Edward Colston is toppled https://t.co/sQ0N2BEugD 

In Seattle, a man drove his car into a crowd of protesters, then shoots and injures a demonstrator 9/17 https://t.co/WI5yAUVz1M

name: Reuters
text:
June 8, 9: Floyd’s casket is displayed in Houston, drawing thousands. 

Democrats introduce police reform legislation, and kneel in the Capitol building. 

George Floyd is buried in Houston https://t.co/22n58jxXIN 10/17 https://t.co/1hymAnQgjN

name: Reuters
text:
June 10-12: NASCAR bans the Confederate flag. 

Minneapolis votes to replace the police department with a community-led public safety system. 

Rayshard Brooks is killed by an officer after falling asleep in a Wendy’s restaurant drive-through lane https://t.co/5JehCRXRNa 11/17 https://t.co/5lzZnxjcLY

name: Reuters
text:
June 13-15: Protesters burn down the Wendy’s where Rayshard Brooks was killed https://t.co/36fvlq2rV3

UK Prime Minister Johnson announces a government commission on racism and ethnic disparities in education, health and criminal justice https://t.co/XxQ8YPsKFo 12/17 https://t.co/1RDI679Mwe

name: Reuters
text:

Colorado becomes one of the first U.S. states to strip police officers of qualified immunity https://t.co/aj8bNnwlom 13/17

name: Reuters
text:
June 20: Trump holds a rally in Tulsa, Oklahoma, where white residents murdered an estimated 300 Black Americans 99 years ago. 

TikTok users and K-pop fans took partial credit for inflating attendance expectations https://t.co/Xe4ynwM9Rw 14/17 https://t.co/WuPybsXO9h
